In this proclamation, President Donald Trump emphasizes the importance of education in empowering students and developing a strong workforce and informed citizenry. He acknowledges the challenges faced by students, teachers, and administrators during the COVID-19 pandemic but emphasizes the importance of reopening schools for the well-being of children. The President highlights his administration's efforts to ensure safe classrooms and provide resources for schools. He also discusses the need for greater flexibility and choice in education, allowing parents to have more control over their children's education. President Trump celebrates American Education Week and recognizes the teachers, community leaders, parents, and advocates who contribute to shaping the future of the country. The proclamation concludes by calling on states and communities to support high-quality education to meet the needs of all students.